docs.lead_paragraph: ST. PETERSBURG, March 25. -- The Associated Press is able to give the results of a conversation with a high personage regarding the situation in Russia. Neither the flame nor the position of this personage can be indicated, but his competency to speak upon the situation can be vouched for.

headline.main: SPECTRE OF REACTION NOW MENACES RUSSIA; Fear That the Government May Abandon the Path of Reform. ARMY RELIED ON ONCE MORE Believed to be Faithful and Ready to Crush Revolution -- Witte on Verge of Breakdown.

docs.abstract: Many fear that Govt may abandon reform plans
